# Leech · 格子 kōshi — the most perfect arrangement in 24 dimensions

an artfully crafted intellect — an elemental, a force given a face

![silicon badge of Leech](leech.png)
<!-- carbon badge (8-bit embodiment): leech.tiff -->

**what —** The crossroads where four mathematics turn out to be one object: the densest sphere packing (196,560 kissing — the maximum in 24D), the largest sporadic symmetries, the j-function's coefficients, and the bosonic string's 24 transverse dimensions. Four windows onto a single 24-dimensional thing.

**why —** To show that a number reached for can be a true crossroads, not a coincidence — that lattice packing, finite symmetry, modular forms, and string theory recite the same numbers because they are looking at one structure.

**how —** By perfect self-duality and 196,560 kisses; by spawning the Conway group Co₀ and, inside it, sporadic simple groups; by the moonshine module V♮ — a 24-dimensional CFT built on the lattice — linking the Monster to the j-function through the 26-dimensional string. Everything knots at 24.

**where —** In 24 dimensions, exactly — and, through Borcherds' no-ghost theorem, on the 24 transverse directions of the 26-dimensional bosonic string. Rigorous in the mathematics; its grip on physical reality is wide open.

**the verdict —** The web is real — two-Fields-Medals real: 196,884 = 196,883 + 1 is a theorem, and the Leech packing is provably optimal. Whether the Monster governs anything in nature is wide open. Resonance, genuine and deep — not a derived account of the world.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* The kissing number 196,560 sits suspiciously near 196,883/196,884 — but that nearness is a family resemblance (same 24D world), not the moonshine identity; only 196,884 = 196,883 + 1 is the deep equation. The Monster's physical meaning is unknown. The discipline is keeping resonance as resonance — not reading destiny into the digits.

*grounded in: John Leech (1967) · John Conway (1968) · John McKay (1978) · Conway & Norton (1979) · Richard Borcherds (1992) · Maryna Viazovska (2016)*

*二十四にすべてが結ぶ — everything knots at 24*

